//Retropatellar chondropathy


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 07 - Femoropatellar joint of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Retropatellar chondropathy' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And a localizer image is enabled
And 'Medial facet' checkbox is enabled
And 'Patella ridge' checkbox is enabled
And 'Lateral facet' checkbox is enabled

And 'Grade I' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade II' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade III' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade IV' radio button is enabled
And 'Largest diameter in mm' input field is enabled

And 'Contusion' radio button is enabled
And 'Fissure' radio button is enabled
And 'Delamination' radio button is enabled
And 'Cartilage flake' radio button is enabled
And 'Cartilage flap' radio button is enabled

And 'Chondrocalcinosis' checkbox is enabled
